paris-153.def: World Bank Governance Indicator on Regulatory Quality. This indicator measures the perceptions of the ability of the government to formulate and implement sound policies and regulations that permit and promote private sector development.
paris-153.name: Regulatory quality
paris-153.source: WGI are produced by Daniel Kaufmann (Natural Resource Governance Institute and Brookings Institution) and Aart Kraay (World Bank Development Research Group).
